# 20. Ready Steady

Toya: Akito, you were listening?
Akito: Yeah. I asked Ken to leave his phone on.
Toya: ...I see.
Toya: I bet you're disappointed that the person with the weakest resolve ended up being the one right next to you this whole time.
Akito: .....
Toya: I was never able to be as dedicated as you were about chasing your dream.
Akito: Y'know... I've never seen anyone so crazy that they can practice from morning until night the way you do.
Toya: .....
Toya: I thought maybe it'd help me be worthy of standing on stage with you.
Akito: Toya...
Toya: The only skills I have are those I learned from playing classical music. And even that was too much for me, so I ran away.
Toya: Practicing like that was the only way for someone like me to have any chance of getting up on stage with someone as serious about their singing as you.
Akito: You're...so serious it's stupid...
Toya: It's true that I felt like I could be my real self whenever I was singing with you, and I'm thankful for that.
Toya: But that's all the more reason I can't stay here. There's nothing more I can do to help you fulfill your dream.
Akito: Is that how you really feel?
Toya: ...What?
Akito: I don't care what your reasons for starting were or that you were running away from classical music! All that matters is what you really want to do now!
Toya: .....
Akito: You remember right after we formed BAD DOGS when that guy told us we had spirit but no skill?
Akito: I remember getting really upset, but you never said a thing.
Akito: Friends would normally try to cheer each other up in that sort of situation, but you didn't say a word.
Akito: You just kept practicing with me.
Akito: The look on your face said, We're better than this. We'll show them what we can really do.
Toya: .....
Akito: I've only made it this far because you were with me!
Akito: You love music. So much that it's ridiculous! I know more than anyone how serious you are.
Akito: The only reason I was able to chase my dream of surpassing RAD WEEKEND was because you were there to listen to me! I don't waver because I know you believe in me!
Toya: But Akito, I...
Akito: Shut up with the excuses already!
Akito: Why can't you get it through your thick skull! I have no intention of teaming up with anyone but you!
Toya: !!
Akito: What do your true feelings tell you right now? Do you really not want to do this with me anymore?!
Akito: Is there no part of you that wants to get up on that stage with me?! If there is, then somewhere in there you must have the same dream of surpassing RAD WEEKEND that I have!
Toya: !!
Toya: Of course I want to!
Toya: You have no idea how many times I've thought about just focusing on chasing your dream with you!
Akito: Toya... So you finally admit it.
Akito: If that's what you want, then just do it.
Toya: But...
Akito: Nope, that's enough out of you. Stop overthinking every little thing. I want to work with you, and you want to work with me.
Akito: All that's left is to realize our dream together. Isn't that enough?
Toya: Are you...really okay with that?
Akito: Yeah.
Toya: Is it really okay for someone with such weak resolve to stand up there with you?
Akito: Your resolve isn't weak. You may think it is, but to me, you're the best singing partner a guy could ask for.
Toya: Akito...
Toya: If you want to do it, then just go for it...
Toya: ...I get it now. So the answer was really that simple all along.
Akito: You know, for someone who's so good at school, you sure are stupid.
Akito: Oh well. Starting tomorrow, we're going to be making up for lost time, partner.
Akito: Then we'll organize an event that'll surpass RAD WEEKEND. Got it?
Toya: Yeah.
An: Now that that's all worked out, can I take your order?
Akito: What?!
Kohane: A-An?
Akito: How long have you two been standing there?! Have you been listening this entire time?
An: You're the one who ignored us and just kept talking. Besides, you were on such a roll that we didn't want to interrupt you.
An: I'm happy for you two.
Kohane: Yeah! Aoyagi, this means you'll be able to sing with Shinonome again!
Toya: Azusawa, Shiraishi.
Toya: Sorry for making you two worry about me.
Toya: I've made up my mind. I'm going to help Akito surpass RAD WEEKEND.
An: Hey, now! We're the ones who are going to surpass RAD WEEKEND! Don't go getting ahead of yourselves!
Kohane: Hehe!
???: <So you've finally found them.>
An: Did you hear a voice just now?
Kohane: Huh? Untitled is flashing again...
An: Hey, you're right!
Akito: Untitled? You guys know about that too?
Kohane: Ah!
Toya: Where are we?
